Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
display_timing_map(25.10)                            display_timing_map(25.10)

Name
       display_timing_map  - Sets color-coded slack threshold values for worst
       timing paths

Syntax
       display_timing_map

       [-help]

       {[-step float  -threshold float ] -check_type {setup | hold}] | -clear}

       Sets color-coded slack threshold values for worst timing paths.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each display_timing_map parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man display_timing_map

       -check_type {setup | hold}
              Specifies the check type for timing paths.  The  possible  argu-
              ments are setup and  hold.

       -clear Clears the timing slack threshold values.

       -step  Sets the step value.

       -threshold
              Sets  color-coded slack threshold values for worst timing paths.
              You can specify a range of threshold values. When specified, the
              instances as seen on the Timing Debug form are  color-coded  ac-
              cording to the worst timing slack threshold value.

              For  information  on timing map, see "Display Timing Map" in the
              Innovus Menu Reference Guide .

Examples
              * The following example sets a threshold value of -1, for  setup
                timing check:

                display_timing_map -step 0.2 -threshold -1 -check_type setup

